Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{3} into 2cm chunks (peeling optional).

Pop the chunks onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste} then season with @paprika{2%sachet}, @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Toss to coat and spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

== Chorizo Salsa ==

Season the @21 Day Aged Irish Sirloin Steak{250%g} with salt and pepper.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat and its packaging.

Peel and grate the @garlic{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Chop the @tomato{2} into 1cm chunks.

Take one-quarter of the @salad leaves{40%g}(rocket) and finely chop—we'll use this as a herb for the salsa. Set the remaining rocket aside for later.

Place a large #pan{} over medium-high heat (without oil).

Once hot, fry the @chorizo{100%g} until it starts to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the garlic and half the tomatoes. Cook together for ~{1%minute} more.

Remove from the heat then stir in the @apple cider vinegar{1%sachet} and @oil{1%tbsp} (double for 4p).

Transfer to a #small bowl{}, allow to cool for ~{1%minute} and then stir through the chopped rocket.

== Sirloin Steak ==

Wipe the pan and return to high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, fry the sirloin until browned. Cook ~{1-2%minutes} on each side for medium-rare.

Cook for another ~{1-2%minutes} on each side if you want it more well-done.

> IMPORTANT: Meat is safe to eat when outside is browned.

Once cooked to your liking, transfer to a #board{}, cover and allow to rest.

== Rocket Salad ==

Pop the remaining rocket into a #salad bowl{} along with the remaining tomatoes.

Dress the salad with a drizzle of oil and a pinch of salt and pepper. Toss to coat.

Divide the salad between your plates.

== Assembly ==

Plate up the paprika roast potatoes next to the rocket salad.

Thinly slice the sirloin and arrange alongside.

Finish by spooning the chorizo salsa over the sirloin steak.